CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 2, 1974 reads: "Trinity Cites Rev. Strong - In a beautiful banquet setting, the Rev. and Mrs. Matthew Strong, seated center, were recently honored on his seventh anniversary as pastor of Trinity Baptist Church, Lawrenceville. Mrs. Estelle Brown, the chairman, is presenting a token of appreciation to the pastor, for the church.  Special guests at table include Rev. and Mrs. Lewis Jones, left; Rev. and Mrs. Clifton Ruggs, right.  Members of the committee, standing left to right are, Loretta Davis, Ethel Hunter, Thelma Fulton, Margaret Wilkes, Lillie M. Goeffrey and Catherine Kenny. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Rev. and Mrs. Lewis Jones, Rev. and Mrs. Matthew Strong, receiving gift from Estelle Brown, and Rev. and Mrs. Clifton Ruggs; standing: Loretta Davis, Ethel Hunter, Thelma Fulton, Margaret Wilkes, Lillie M. Goeffrey, and Catherine Kenny, gathered behind banquet table for pastoral anniversary at Trinity Baptist Church, Lawrenceville
